            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="864" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.248/3–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-26T19:00:00-04:00">April 26, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. ReLegs 122, March 24, 11 a.m. The project for the establishment of a U.S.
                    military air base at Dhahran has been approved by the British Chiefs of Staff,
                    and they have been requested to inform the British Government of their
                    decision.</p>
                <p>On April 24 the Department asked the British Embassy to request the Foreign
                    Office to instruct the British Minister in Jidda to inform King Ibn Saud of
                    British approval.</p>
                <p>The War Department is now working on further instructions intended for the
                    Legation’s guidance in the impending negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
